   <titleInfo>
      <title>Interview with Martha Ward, 2017-04-20</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>Interview with Martha Ward, resident of Gatlinburg. Ward discusses the day of the fire and the activities of several community members. Starting with the efforts at Park Vista during and after the fire, she also recounts the assistance given by a neighbor Sandy Vineyard. She then shares the actions of Joel B. Cox to save a school bus and provide transportation during the fire. This is a representative quote from the interview: "There was a huge propane tank right beside our house at the hardware store. And when we heard the explosion, those of use who could walk went outside, and there was fire raining out of the sky."</abstract>
